.TH "pcpu_alloc" 9 "pcpu_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcpu_alloc \- the percpu allocator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __percpu *" pcpu_alloc
.BI "(size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t align "  ","
.BI "bool reserved "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
size of area to allocate in bytes
.IP "align" 12
alignment of area (max PAGE_SIZE)
.IP "reserved" 12
allocate from the reserved chunk if available
.IP "gfp" 12
allocation flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate percpu area of \fIsize\fP bytes aligned at \fIalign\fP.  If \fIgfp\fP doesn't
contain GFP_KERNEL, the allocation is atomic. If \fIgfp\fP has __GFP_NOWARN
then no warning will be triggered on invalid or failed allocation
requests.
.SH "RETURN"
Percpu pointer to the allocated area on success, NULL on failure.
